answers.body_markdown:
Rather than using `:before`, you can create the arrow using `clip-path`

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: true console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-css --&gt;

    .arrow {
      height: 20px;
      width: 20px;
      clip-path: polygon(0 50%, 100% 100%, 100% 0);
      background: red;
    }

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    &lt;div class=&quot;arrow&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

Now, you can use [ElementRef][1] to get hold of the `fs-modal` element and change the top value for `.arrow` class

[Updated StackBlitz Demo][2]


  [1]: https://angular.io/api/core/ElementRef
  [2]: https://stackblitz.com/edit/angular-ytnzmy

